The victim was taking inventory at the Lizard Rock lodge when a white Toyota bakkie with about five men pulled up. One of them was dressed in a police uniform. The men stated they were busy with an investigation. Upon entering onto the property, they tied up the victim and robbed the business of some cash. They then took him to his house, located a few hundred metres from the lodge, where they tied up his wife and robbed them of other valuables. ALSO READ: Inspiring a community of young plant lovers Albert Gryvenstein from Bossies Community Justice confirmed the incident. After he had arrived on the scene, he called Hi-Tech to help block off the exit points. So far they have not found anything. The police and forensics team are on the scene. The white bakkie did not have licence plates. This is a developing story. Lowvelder will keep you updated.